        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 4:27PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mercer, or 12 miles east of Brownsville, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Neely, Bells, Malesus, Fruitvale, Bemis, Adair, Huntersville, Gum
Flat, Jackson, Westover, Roberts, Carroll, Gilmore, Denmark,
Leighton, Mercer, Oakfield, and Uptonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
